                  <occupation type="literary"> writer </occupation>
               <birth notBefore="1892" notAfter="1893"> He was born in <placeName ref="LOC2272DabraG"/> between <date>1892-1893</date>. </birth>
                  
                  
                  <floruit notBefore="1906" notAfter="1947">
                     He was a prolific writer with a pronounced background in traditional church education and a pioneer of Ethiopian theatre and Amharic drama. 
                     He was first appointed as <roleName type="title">mač̣ane</roleName> and <roleName type="title">qaññgetā</roleName>, later the head of 
                     <placeName ref="LOC2646DemahG"/>. In <date>1917/1918</date> he became <roleName type="title">dabtarā</roleName> and later  
                     <roleName type="title">ʾaggāfāri</roleName> of <placeName ref="LOC2271DabraG"/>. 
                     In <date>1923/24 he was employed as an Amharic teacher at <persName ref="PRS7006Menilek"/> Secondary School where he started his first lietrary works. </date>
                   </floruit>
                  
               <death notBefore="1946" notAfter="1947"> He died in <placeName ref="LOC1216AddisA"/> between<date>1946-1947</date>.</death>
                  
